    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for any low-growing tree or other woody plant that produces several stems from the base. The term is also used specifically for scrubland vegetation found in southern Australia typically composed primarily of woody shrubs and trees of the genus Eucalyptus.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
